1
00:00:06,027 --> 00:00:07,018
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:07,019 --> 00:00:08,661
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:10,131 --> 00:00:11,881
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:14,752 --> 00:00:15,710
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:15,711 --> 00:00:17,024
(QUACKS)

6
00:00:17,862 --> 00:00:18,970
♪ Adventure Time ♪

7
00:00:18,971 --> 00:00:20,304
♪ Come on, grab your friends ♪

8
00:00:20,305 --> 00:00:23,057
♪ We'll go to very distant lands ♪

9
00:00:23,058 --> 00:00:25,309
♪ With Jake the dog and Finn the human ♪

10
00:00:25,310 --> 00:00:27,103
♪ The fun will never end ♪

11
00:00:27,104 --> 00:00:29,122
♪ It's Adventure Time ♪

12
00:00:29,611 --> 00:00:32,508
Sync and corrections by kaysukri

13
00:00:36,738 --> 00:00:38,872
Yeah! (CHUCKLES)

14
00:00:38,873 --> 00:00:39,939
Whoo-hoo!

15
00:00:39,940 --> 00:00:41,207
(LAUGHS)

16
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:42,809
Yes. This is a hoot.

17
00:00:42,810 --> 00:00:44,244
(CHEERING)

18
00:00:44,245 --> 00:00:47,231
And the winner of the
three-legged race is...

19
00:00:47,232 --> 00:00:48,532
not us!

20
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:49,600
(CHUCKLES)

21
00:00:49,601 --> 00:00:51,736
But we ran a fair race, Kim Kil Whan.

22
00:00:51,737 --> 00:00:52,937
Yes, quite.

23
00:00:52,938 --> 00:00:54,171
Heh, heh.

24
00:00:54,172 --> 00:00:56,007
Of course, we could have murdered them,

25
00:00:56,008 --> 00:00:57,475
but I was holding back.

26
00:00:57,476 --> 00:01:00,244
I'm glad you didn't show off, Dad.

27
00:01:00,245 --> 00:01:01,746
Thanks.

28
00:01:02,348 --> 00:01:03,948
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

29
00:01:03,949 --> 00:01:05,516
(CLEARS THROAT)

30
00:01:05,517 --> 00:01:08,819
Thanks to my team of awesomely
talented sales associates

31
00:01:08,820 --> 00:01:14,892
and also my father, Jake, who's
visiting us this year...

32
00:01:14,893 --> 00:01:16,894
this has been the most successful

33
00:01:16,895 --> 00:01:21,432
animal sports/picnic
socializing event ever.

34
00:01:21,433 --> 00:01:22,800
Uh, whoo-hoo.

35
00:01:22,801 --> 00:01:24,802
ALL: Whoo-hoo!

36
00:01:24,803 --> 00:01:29,073
Wow. Really nice deviled egg
presentation this year, Steve.

37
00:01:29,074 --> 00:01:30,474
Mmm.

38
00:01:30,475 --> 00:01:32,343
Dad, I'm glad you stuck around.

39
00:01:32,344 --> 00:01:36,138
I confess I had an ulterior
motive for inviting you.

40
00:01:36,139 --> 00:01:39,016
I really need your advice on something.

41
00:01:39,017 --> 00:01:40,593
My advice?

42
00:01:42,822 --> 00:01:44,021
Parenting advice.

43
00:01:44,022 --> 00:01:46,657
I don't know how to deal
with my daughter, Bronwyn.

44
00:01:47,051 --> 00:01:48,993
I have a granddaughter?

45
00:01:48,994 --> 00:01:50,375
Psych, I knew that.

46
00:01:50,376 --> 00:01:52,062
What's the problem, mijo.

47
00:01:52,063 --> 00:01:54,899
Bronwyn is not doing well at school.

48
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:57,501
She seems to be busy enough
with homework when she's here,

49
00:01:57,502 --> 00:01:59,136
but her grades are slipping.

50
00:01:59,689 --> 00:02:02,473
And her teacher says she keeps
falling asleep at her desk.

51
00:02:02,474 --> 00:02:04,475
Why is she so unengaged?

52
00:02:04,476 --> 00:02:07,178
And how can I manage her
towards financial success

53
00:02:07,179 --> 00:02:08,813
if she's that unengaged?

54
00:02:08,814 --> 00:02:10,681
I thought you might have some insight

55
00:02:10,682 --> 00:02:13,284
because of your teenage
kind of lifestyle.

56
00:02:15,855 --> 00:02:18,956
What say we rifle through her
biz next time she's out?

57
00:02:18,957 --> 00:02:20,558
Well, I'm no snoop,

58
00:02:20,559 --> 00:02:24,395
but I found these unusual
graphics in her recycling bin.

59
00:02:24,396 --> 00:02:25,763
What do you make of these?

60
00:02:25,764 --> 00:02:27,331
Oh.

61
00:02:27,332 --> 00:02:28,866
Mm-hmm.

62
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,034
Ahh.

63
00:02:30,035 --> 00:02:31,669
What are you thinking?

64
00:02:31,670 --> 00:02:33,992
Not sure yet. I'll have to sleep on it.

65
00:02:34,674 --> 00:02:37,497
I'll let you know tomorrow
if I think of anything.

66
00:02:38,728 --> 00:02:39,480
Weird.

67
00:02:42,115 --> 00:02:43,647
(BAT SQUEAKING)

68
00:03:02,268 --> 00:03:03,934
- Whoo-hoo!
- (LAUGHTER)

69
00:03:03,935 --> 00:03:06,337
- Yeah!
- Oh, man!

70
00:03:09,308 --> 00:03:11,709
(CHEERING)

71
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:13,411
(CHANTING) Bronwyn! Bronwyn! Bronwyn!

72
00:03:13,412 --> 00:03:14,445
Nice one, Bronwyn!

73
00:03:14,446 --> 00:03:17,181
(WHISTLING)

74
00:03:17,182 --> 00:03:19,127
Classic Bronwyn.

75
00:03:20,086 --> 00:03:22,186
Hey, Bronwyn, isn't that your dad?

76
00:03:22,731 --> 00:03:24,891
Nope. That's my granddad.

77
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:28,526
What? You here to bust me?

78
00:03:29,121 --> 00:03:32,293
Nah, I'm just here to skate.

79
00:03:32,294 --> 00:03:33,877
Yeah, okay.

80
00:03:35,130 --> 00:03:36,606
Show me some moves.

81
00:03:41,841 --> 00:03:43,107
Noice!

82
00:03:43,108 --> 00:03:44,508
- Yeah.
- Pretty good moves.

83
00:03:44,509 --> 00:03:47,545
You're actually kinda
cool, for a gwampa.

84
00:03:47,546 --> 00:03:48,779
Thank you, thank you.

85
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:51,682
Thank you. I value your opinion.

86
00:03:51,683 --> 00:03:54,552
(LAUGHS) That's a spot-on KKW.

87
00:03:54,553 --> 00:03:56,274
(LAUGHS) Yeah.

88
00:03:56,989 --> 00:03:58,923
Um, that reminds me.

89
00:03:58,924 --> 00:04:01,105
We're supposed to talk about
getting your grades up

90
00:04:01,106 --> 00:04:03,291
- in school or something.
- What?

91
00:04:03,292 --> 00:04:05,067
We're worried about your, um,

92
00:04:05,068 --> 00:04:07,031
financial success!

93
00:04:07,032 --> 00:04:08,299
I knew it.

94
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,834
You're not cool!

95
00:04:09,835 --> 00:04:12,136
- You're just like Dad!
- What?

96
00:04:12,137 --> 00:04:15,573
I mean, hey, I love your dad,
but we're nothing alike.

97
00:04:15,574 --> 00:04:19,243
It looks like this round
gramps is a real square.

98
00:04:19,244 --> 00:04:21,545
(LAUGHTER)

99
00:04:21,546 --> 00:04:23,414
I'm not a square.

100
00:04:23,415 --> 00:04:24,939
But now I am.

101
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:26,851
Whoa! Radical!

102
00:04:26,852 --> 00:04:28,552
(LAUGHTER)

103
00:04:28,553 --> 00:04:30,955
- How'd you do that?
- Do another one!

104
00:04:30,956 --> 00:04:32,990
I'm an old tree.

105
00:04:32,991 --> 00:04:34,291
(LAUGHTER)

106
00:04:34,292 --> 00:04:36,627
An equestrian statue.

107
00:04:36,628 --> 00:04:38,937
Jake, are you going to
stay here all night?

108
00:04:39,298 --> 00:04:41,065
What? They like me.

109
00:04:41,066 --> 00:04:43,133
They like my ageless
style and everything.

110
00:04:43,134 --> 00:04:44,335
Hmm.

111
00:04:44,336 --> 00:04:46,804
But hark! What's that I hear?

112
00:04:46,805 --> 00:04:50,374
(FARTS)

113
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:52,109
Bronwyn beefed it.

114
00:04:52,110 --> 00:04:55,179
(LAUGHTER)

115
00:04:55,180 --> 00:04:57,475
Y-you're the fart.

116
00:04:57,476 --> 00:04:58,916
What? No.

117
00:04:58,917 --> 00:05:00,017
Old fart.

118
00:05:00,018 --> 00:05:01,399
I'm cool!

119
00:05:03,823 --> 00:05:06,490
Son, it's worse than we thought.

120
00:05:06,491 --> 00:05:09,026
Oh, Koo. Is it black magic?

121
00:05:09,027 --> 00:05:11,262
A cursed ring? An investment scam?

122
00:05:11,263 --> 00:05:12,530
Worse!

123
00:05:12,531 --> 00:05:14,398
I tried real-talking
with Bronwyn last night,

124
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:16,300
and now she thinks I'm a square!

125
00:05:16,301 --> 00:05:19,003
I feel like you're losing
sight of the point here, Dad.

126
00:05:19,004 --> 00:05:21,539
Pretty much everyone
thinks I'm great, right?

127
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:23,674
Maybe stay away from my daughter.

128
00:05:23,675 --> 00:05:25,009
Don't worry, Son.

129
00:05:25,010 --> 00:05:28,279
I won't rest until Bronwyn
realizes how cool I am!

130
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:30,080
But what about...

131
00:05:30,081 --> 00:05:32,149
(GRUMBLES) Dad.

132
00:05:32,985 --> 00:05:36,520
- I got this! I got this!
- Whoo-hoo!

133
00:05:36,521 --> 00:05:38,289
Oh, Glob! I don't!

134
00:05:38,290 --> 00:05:39,723
(LAUGHTER)

135
00:05:39,724 --> 00:05:41,240
JAKE: Fellow dudes!

136
00:05:41,694 --> 00:05:43,761
Old cheeseballs is back.

137
00:05:43,762 --> 00:05:46,196
Ow-ow-ow-ow-ow-ow-ow.

138
00:05:46,197 --> 00:05:47,464
Check it out, kids!

139
00:05:47,465 --> 00:05:49,541
I brought my roommate! He's 16!

140
00:05:50,369 --> 00:05:52,369
That's so old.

141
00:05:52,370 --> 00:05:54,306
Do something cool.

142
00:05:54,307 --> 00:05:56,206
- No, I'm sleep...
- Here, play your flute.

143
00:05:56,207 --> 00:05:57,241
Kids love flute.

144
00:05:57,242 --> 00:05:59,510
Wha... (FOOMP!)

145
00:05:59,511 --> 00:06:02,546
(FLUTE MELODY PLAYS)

146
00:06:05,718 --> 00:06:08,419
Ugh. Is that solo flute?

147
00:06:08,420 --> 00:06:09,887
Yo, that stinks nasty.

148
00:06:09,888 --> 00:06:12,590
(BOOING) Uh-oh, kids hate flute.

149
00:06:12,591 --> 00:06:14,525
But, they love mash-ups!

150
00:06:14,526 --> 00:06:16,961
(BEATBOXES)

151
00:06:16,962 --> 00:06:20,531
Whoa, Gwampa is turning it up!

152
00:06:20,532 --> 00:06:23,434
(CHEERING)

153
00:06:23,435 --> 00:06:26,937
(CHANTING) Jake! Jake! Jake!

154
00:06:26,938 --> 00:06:28,339
Math! (SNORING)

155
00:06:28,340 --> 00:06:30,541
This dude don't give a dump.

156
00:06:30,542 --> 00:06:33,410
Dang, you're, like, like a cool gwampa.

157
00:06:33,411 --> 00:06:34,878
Yes!

158
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:38,282
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

159
00:06:38,283 --> 00:06:39,880
(SQUEAKS)

160
00:06:40,806 --> 00:06:41,952
Hey, guys.

161
00:06:41,953 --> 00:06:44,375
Have you ever heard music like this?

162
00:06:46,158 --> 00:06:47,257
(GULP!)

163
00:06:47,258 --> 00:06:48,855
(COUGHING)

164
00:06:48,856 --> 00:06:50,753
Way to choke, Bron.

165
00:06:52,194 --> 00:06:53,691
Yo, how about a duet?

166
00:06:53,692 --> 00:06:55,633
(BEATBOXING)

167
00:06:55,634 --> 00:06:58,305
(COUGHING CONTINUES)

168
00:06:58,306 --> 00:06:59,503
(LAUGHTER)

169
00:06:59,504 --> 00:07:01,566
Even Gwamps can't save you, Bron!

170
00:07:05,211 --> 00:07:06,477
B, why'd you stop?

171
00:07:06,478 --> 00:07:08,864
They're laughing at me.

172
00:07:09,335 --> 00:07:12,449
Hey, come on guys,
don't bust on Bronwyn.

173
00:07:12,450 --> 00:07:14,828
Bronwyn's cool. I can vouch for her.

174
00:07:15,259 --> 00:07:17,254
Now let's all watch me skate!

175
00:07:17,255 --> 00:07:18,455
Whoo!

176
00:07:18,456 --> 00:07:20,157
(LAUGHTER)

177
00:07:20,158 --> 00:07:22,192
BRONWYN: Weak!

178
00:07:22,193 --> 00:07:23,754
(COUGHS)

179
00:07:23,755 --> 00:07:26,655
I can skate way better
better than you, Jake.

180
00:07:27,266 --> 00:07:29,800
TOGETHER: Ooooooh.

181
00:07:32,471 --> 00:07:34,238
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

182
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:36,974
(THUNDER CRASHES)

183
00:07:36,975 --> 00:07:39,543
I challenge you to a thrash off.

184
00:07:39,544 --> 00:07:40,911
(COUGHS)

185
00:07:40,912 --> 00:07:43,580
- Ohh!
- Buh?

186
00:07:43,581 --> 00:07:46,641
The winner is declared undeniably cool.

187
00:07:46,986 --> 00:07:50,154
The loser is banned from the skate park.

188
00:07:50,155 --> 00:07:51,722
I can live with that.

189
00:07:51,723 --> 00:07:52,940
Whatever.

190
00:07:54,026 --> 00:07:56,860
Dude, you're really gonna
ban your own granddaughter

191
00:07:56,861 --> 00:07:58,529
from her own skate park?

192
00:07:58,530 --> 00:08:00,097
Man, I hope so.

193
00:08:08,474 --> 00:08:09,789
Hmm.

194
00:08:12,478 --> 00:08:14,278
Yeah, real cool.

195
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:16,680
FOX: Hey, it's time!

196
00:08:21,887 --> 00:08:22,862
Nice!

197
00:08:23,823 --> 00:08:27,257
(CHANTING) Gwampa! Gwampa! Gwampa!

198
00:08:27,258 --> 00:08:31,128
Bronwyn, did you see my cool new hair?

199
00:08:31,129 --> 00:08:32,110
Ugh.

200
00:08:33,132 --> 00:08:37,367
Hey!

201
00:08:37,368 --> 00:08:39,603
Welcome to Thrashland.

202
00:08:39,604 --> 00:08:42,106
Are you two ready to thrash?

203
00:08:42,107 --> 00:08:46,123
From here, you must skate the
entire length of the park.

204
00:08:46,124 --> 00:08:48,378
First, grind down the ramp,

205
00:08:48,379 --> 00:08:49,880
through the bar maze,

206
00:08:49,881 --> 00:08:51,882
past the big-armed worm,

207
00:08:51,883 --> 00:08:53,517
through the junkyard,

208
00:08:53,518 --> 00:08:55,319
over the log swamp,

209
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:59,156
and finally cross the finish
at the bottomless pit of love.

210
00:08:59,157 --> 00:09:01,091
(ALL GASP)

211
00:09:01,835 --> 00:09:04,695
Hey, Jake, no weird magic biz.

212
00:09:04,696 --> 00:09:06,864
Heh-heh, same to you.

213
00:09:06,865 --> 00:09:09,967
Remember, you're an instant
fart if you eat it.

214
00:09:09,968 --> 00:09:12,136
Take it away, flute man.

215
00:09:13,973 --> 00:09:16,073
This is a terrible idea.

216
00:09:19,912 --> 00:09:22,846
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

217
00:09:35,594 --> 00:09:37,261
Whoa... oof!

218
00:09:37,262 --> 00:09:38,428
(GROANS)

219
00:09:38,429 --> 00:09:40,397
(PANTING)

220
00:09:43,235 --> 00:09:44,735
Huh?

221
00:09:46,906 --> 00:09:48,806
Oh, dang! I love you, Bronwyn!

222
00:09:48,807 --> 00:09:51,909
Whoa, cool! Time to ice this cake!

223
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:54,745
Whoo! Jake, no!

224
00:09:54,746 --> 00:09:56,446
It took me months to make that jump!

225
00:09:56,447 --> 00:09:57,648
You're gonna biff it!

226
00:09:57,649 --> 00:09:58,816
I won't biff it!

227
00:09:58,817 --> 00:10:01,652
I'm the coolest guy aliiiiii...

228
00:10:03,556 --> 00:10:04,655
(THUD!)

229
00:10:04,656 --> 00:10:05,756
(FARTS)

230
00:10:05,757 --> 00:10:07,075
Grandpa!

231
00:10:07,993 --> 00:10:09,493
You're cool! You're cool!

232
00:10:09,494 --> 00:10:10,897
Just please be okay, Grandpa!

233
00:10:10,898 --> 00:10:12,096
Interference!

234
00:10:12,097 --> 00:10:13,497
Interference!

235
00:10:13,498 --> 00:10:14,911
That means I win, right?

236
00:10:14,912 --> 00:10:16,600
- Dad!
- Dad?

237
00:10:16,601 --> 00:10:18,646
- Are you okay?
- I'm great.

238
00:10:18,647 --> 00:10:20,245
She admitted it.

239
00:10:22,317 --> 00:10:23,449
(GROANS)

240
00:10:23,450 --> 00:10:24,851
Whoo.

241
00:10:24,852 --> 00:10:26,519
Jake!

242
00:10:27,956 --> 00:10:29,180
Bronwyn...

243
00:10:30,825 --> 00:10:34,560
look, I can see that skating
is important to you.

244
00:10:34,561 --> 00:10:36,828
And you seem very talented at it,

245
00:10:36,829 --> 00:10:40,066
but you're still going to have
to pull it together in school.

246
00:10:40,913 --> 00:10:43,136
Okay, I did get carried away.

247
00:10:43,137 --> 00:10:44,404
I'm sorry.

248
00:10:44,798 --> 00:10:45,972
I'm sorry, too.

249
00:10:45,973 --> 00:10:48,295
I should have just come to you myself,

250
00:10:48,296 --> 00:10:51,210
instead of sending
your cool grandfather.

251
00:10:51,211 --> 00:10:54,847
I just thought you wouldn't
listen to a square like me.

252
00:10:54,848 --> 00:10:58,751
Nah, I mean you're not cool,
but you're not uncool.

253
00:10:58,752 --> 00:11:01,721
Kim Kil Whan! Bronwyn! Look at me!

254
00:11:01,722 --> 00:11:03,756
(GRUNTS)

255
00:11:03,757 --> 00:11:05,224
Time to go home.

256
00:11:05,226 --> 00:11:08,506
Not the swan, that's where
the pups came from.
